\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6}{\ignorespaces Pillar\nobreakspace  {}N: atomic-clock consistency of the DSC $1/\qopname  \relax o{ln}^2$ ansatz. Forest plot of best-fit $\Gamma $ from Pillars\nobreakspace  {}A and\nobreakspace  {}K, with the atomic-clock bound $|\Gamma | < 1.9 \times 10^4$ shown as a green band (off-scale, see notebook). All cosmologically-supported $\Gamma $ values lie 3$\times 10^3$ below the bound. The DSC $1/\qopname  \relax o{ln}^2$ ansatz is automatically consistent with present-epoch laboratory tests of $\dot  \alpha /\alpha $, while still permitting cosmological signal accumulation at $z \sim 1$--$3$.}}{23}{figure.6}\protected@file@percent }
